#[head=2]Aqueous, Haematic and Plasmic Substrate Responses in Polychromatic Xenocolloid Fragments — Preliminary Observations[/head]
The following observations document substrate reactions in isolated xenocolloid fragments across multiple chromatic classifications. Fragments were subjected to aqueous, haematic, and plasmic injections, respectively. Results are preliminary and non-comprehensive — classification and testing are ongoing. Inconclusive results indicate observed but unverified reactions requiring replication under controlled conditions.

